    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-16T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-16T07:00:00-05:00" n="52"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d52">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72114a/29</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SPA1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-16T13:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 16, 1918, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received July 17, 11 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3967. Department’s 1557, March 4, 4 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d52fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_24">p. 24</ref>.</note> I am
                    transmitting by mail a communication from German Foreign Office<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d52fn2">Not printed.</note> stating that German Government is
                    disposed to enter into same agreement with American Government regarding defense
                    of prisoners of war under accusation as exists between British and German
                    Governments and French and German Governments. The copy of <hi rend="italic"
                        >note verbale</hi> from German Foreign Office to Netherlands Legation,
                    Berlin, in charge of British interests, giving conditions of agreement, is
                        enclosed.<note n="2" xml:id="d52fn3">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <pb facs="0116" n="32" xml:id="pg_32"/>
                <p>As regarding punishment for attempted escape, German Government is prepared to
                    reach agreement with United States Government and suggests that this question be
                    taken up in proposed prisoners-of-war conference at Berne.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d52fn4">For final arrangements regarding these points see the
                        agreement of Nov, 11, 1918, <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_103">p. 103</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SPA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stovall</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
